Note:
Runa Standard Library: Traceback Utilities

Provides comprehensive utilities for working with stack traces, error reporting, debugging, and exception handling.

Idiomatic Runa code uses natural language operators:
  Try:
            Call some_failing_process()
  Catch Error as e:
            Let trace be format exception with exc as e
            Call print exception with exc as e
            Let stack be extract stack trace
            Let frames be analyze stack frames of stack

For advanced/AI-generated code, use helpers:
  Let result be format with exc as exception and format_type as "detailed"
  Let result be analyze with stack as traceback and analysis_type as "performance"
:End Note

Process called "format_exception" that takes exc as Any returns String:
            Return exception_to_string(exc)

Process called "print_exception" that takes exc as Any returns None:
            Print exception_to_string(exc)
            Return None

Process called "extract_stack" returns List[String]:
            Return current_stack_trace()

Process called "format_stack" that takes stack as List[String] returns String:
            Return format_stack_trace(stack)

Process called "print_stack" that takes stack as List[String] returns None:
            Print format_stack_trace(stack)
            Return None

Process called "extract_stack_frames" returns List[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
